What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Antimicrobial Agent Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Antimicrobial Agent Market

The antimicrobial agent market is expected to gain market growth in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research analyses the market to reach at an estimated value of USD 5180.6 million by 2028 and grow at a CAGR of 9.00% in the above-mentioned forecast period.

Antimicrobial agents are the compounds which are used as disinfectant chemicals to destroy, restrict or slow down the spread of microorganisms such as viruses, bacteria, fungi and protozoans. They are used in several applications and are organic as well as inorganic.

The factors such as increasing usage of these agents for personal care and cosmetics manufacturing and surging demand for antimicrobial packaging are the root cause fueling up the antimicrobial agent market growth rate. Additionally, the increasing prevalence of individuals suffering from allergies and growing areas of applications due to the growth of medical devices consumption will also directly and positively impact the growth rate of the antimicrobial agent market. However, high costs associated with these products and their usage in different applications derail growth of the antimicrobial agent market.

The availability of various policies and regulations regarding the usage of these agents in different applications pose as a major challenge to the growth of the antimicrobial agent market. Stringent regulatory procedures in the developed countries pose as challenge for the marketâ€™s growth.

